# Fix Login and Backend Import Errors

The login page is failing due to a missing `/auth/login` endpoint and an `ImportError` in the backend caused by circular or incorrect imports of [get_current_user](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/dependencies.py#28-70). This plan addresses both issues.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [auth.py](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/routers/auth.py)
- Implement the `@router.post("/login")` endpoint.
- Ensure it uses `bcrypt` for password verification (already in [User](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/models/user.py#20-48) model).
- Set the session cookie on successful login.

#### [MODIFY] [grades.py](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/routers/grades.py)
- Fix the import of [get_current_user](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/dependencies.py#28-70). It should be `from dependencies import get_current_user`, not `from routers.auth import get_current_user`.

#### [MODIFY] [Other Routers]
- Check all other routers in `routers/` for the same incorrect import and fix them.

### Verification Plan

#### Automated Tests
- Run `pytest backend/tests/test_routers/test_auth.py` (if it exists) or create a reproduction script to verify the `/auth/login` endpoint and fix the `ImportError`.
- Restart the backend and check [uvicorn.log](file:///Users/oli/Desktop/CraftCanvas/backend/logs/uvicorn.log) to ensure no more `ImportError` occurs.

#### Manual Verification
- Attempt to login via the frontend UI and verify successful redirection to the dashboard.
- Check the browser console and network tab for any 500 errors or slow requests.
